00:34:39,960 --> 00:34:41,080
Sure.

523
00:34:41,120 --> 00:34:42,840
Here's something you should see.

524
00:34:46,160 --> 00:34:48,880
I like the old deal bet--
Hey!

525
00:34:49,840 --> 00:34:53,920
Ow! That hurt!

526
00:34:54,040 --> 00:34:55,680
HARRY: Like I said,
no good deed goes unpunished.

527
00:34:55,720 --> 00:34:57,440
JEFF: Ain't that the truth?

528
00:34:57,480 --> 00:35:00,600
Remember Mexico, pally?
Mel's little friend?

529
00:35:00,640 --> 00:35:05,000
You see? I've been takin'
lessons like you told me.

530
00:35:05,040 --> 00:35:09,560
Did we or did we not agree you
weren't gonna show your face?

531
00:35:09,600 --> 00:35:12,000
I know what I'm doing, OK?

532
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:16,120
GLORlA:
Smart. Real, real smart.

533
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:18,040
JEFF: You know where I've been
taking lessons?

534
00:35:20,480 --> 00:35:22,240
In jail.

535
00:35:22,280 --> 00:35:24,120
Yuma, Arizona.

536
00:35:25,280 --> 00:35:27,480
Have you ever been to Yuma?

537
00:35:27,520 --> 00:35:29,400
That's where they put me...

538
00:35:29,440 --> 00:35:31,840
after your friend,
Mr. Jack Ames...

539
00:35:31,880 --> 00:35:34,080
had me arrested
for transporting a minor.

540
00:35:34,120 --> 00:35:37,160
You wanna learn to kick ass,
no better place than Yuma.

541
00:35:37,200 --> 00:35:39,560
Is this gonna take all night?

542
00:35:40,360 --> 00:35:43,480
OK. Come on.
I need you to wake up, pally.

543
00:35:43,520 --> 00:35:45,680
Listen.

544
00:35:45,720 --> 00:35:48,320
I want you to tell Mr. Ames...

545
00:35:48,360 --> 00:35:50,080
that this...

546
00:35:50,120 --> 00:35:53,640
is just a down payment
on what he owes me.

547
00:35:55,320 --> 00:35:58,880
Can you remember that, pally?
Hmm?

548
00:35:58,920 --> 00:36:00,080
Hmm?

549
00:36:01,920 --> 00:36:03,880
Are you finished?

550
00:36:03,920 --> 00:36:06,080
JEFF: Yes, I'm finished.

551
00:36:06,120 --> 00:36:07,600
HARRY: Ooh!

552
00:36:07,640 --> 00:36:10,440
GLORlA: Did we or did we not
make a plan?

553
00:36:10,480 --> 00:36:12,640
What is the point
of making a plan...

554
00:36:12,680 --> 00:36:15,200
if you're just gonna
say ""Fuck it""?

555
00:36:15,240 --> 00:36:17,040
JEFF: Why are you
always so negative?

556
00:36:29,120 --> 00:36:31,480
Oh, shit.

557
00:36:33,600 --> 00:36:35,000
Hey!

558
00:36:35,040 --> 00:36:36,600
Hey, chief, wake up!

559
00:36:37,600 --> 00:36:39,480
Hey, wake up, man.

560
00:36:39,520 --> 00:36:42,040
You can't stay here.
The tide is coming in.

561
00:36:43,040 --> 00:36:46,400
Harry. Harry, it's me,
your old partner.

562
00:36:46,440 --> 00:36:48,440
Somebody beat the shit
out of you.

563
00:36:48,480 --> 00:36:51,640
It's lucky I came along.
Otherwise, you would've drowned.

564
00:36:51,680 --> 00:36:53,720
But I saved your life.

565
00:36:53,760 --> 00:36:56,120
Don't worry.
You can thank me later.

566
00:36:59,600 --> 00:37:02,960
REUBEN: I'm sitting in the limo
at the Santa Monica pier--

567
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:05,240
I'm on the job.
Rich kid, sweet-16 party--

568
00:37:05,280 --> 00:37:08,560
and who do I see
but my old partner Harry Ross.

569
00:37:08,640 --> 00:37:11,360
HARRY: We are not partners.
We were never partners.

570
00:37:11,400 --> 00:37:13,440
I'm telling you
how I saved your life.

571
00:37:13,480 --> 00:37:14,960
It's not nice to interrupt.

572
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:16,600
Where was l? Oh, yeah.

573
00:37:16,640 --> 00:37:19,440
So I'm waiting.
I see you go to the beach.

574
00:37:19,480 --> 00:37:21,080
I figure
you're gonna need backup.

575
00:37:21,120 --> 00:37:22,680
I'm cool. I pick my spot.

576
00:37:22,720 --> 00:37:23,800
You what?

577
00:37:23,840 --> 00:37:26,360
REUBEN: I wait,
just like you taught me.

578
00:37:26,400 --> 00:37:29,680
After a while, I see two people
come out from under the pier...

579
00:37:29,760 --> 00:37:31,560
and there was no sign of you.

580
00:37:31,600 --> 00:37:34,480
I think to myself,
hey, this doesn't look so good.

581
00:37:34,520 --> 00:37:37,320
I go down to the beach,
and there you were.

582
00:37:37,360 --> 00:37:39,240
That's when I saved your life.

583
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:41,040
HARRY:
Let me get this straight.

584
00:37:41,080 --> 00:37:43,640
I was getting
the shit kicked out of me...

585
00:37:44,560 --> 00:37:47,880
and you were
in the parking lot waiting?

586
00:37:47,920 --> 00:37:49,800
And you call that backup?

587
00:37:49,840 --> 00:37:52,320
Hey, I got a good look at them.

588
00:37:52,360 --> 00:37:54,560
I got a better look
than you did.

589
00:37:55,640 --> 00:37:57,480
HARRY:
When are you gonna realize...

590
00:37:57,520 --> 00:37:59,560
that I'm not
a private investigator anymore?

591
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:04,560
REUBEN: You can't just quit.
You were the best, the greatest.

592
00:38:04,600 --> 00:38:07,720
OK, maybe not the greatest,
but you were good, man.

593
00:38:07,760 --> 00:38:10,080
We were good.
We were a hell of a team.

594
00:38:10,120 --> 00:38:11,880
Reuben, we were never a team.

595
00:38:11,920 --> 00:38:13,360
Every once in a while...

596
00:38:13,400 --> 00:38:16,240
I gave you some leg work,
which you usually screwed up.

597
00:38:16,280 --> 00:38:17,680
That doesn't make us a team.

598
00:38:18,200 --> 00:38:21,000
Listen, you got to let me in
on this case.

599
00:38:21,040 --> 00:38:22,800
I can't take this job anymore.

600
00:38:22,840 --> 00:38:24,880
If it's not the freeways,
it's the dispatchers.

601
00:38:24,920 --> 00:38:27,600
If it's not the dispatchers,
it's the clients.

602
00:38:27,640 --> 00:38:29,520
Speaking of which,
where are the kids?

603
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:30,720
What kids?

604
00:38:30,760 --> 00:38:32,520
The sweet- 16 kids.

605
00:38:32,560 --> 00:38:35,800
Ay, carajo.
You think they're still there?

606
00:38:36,920 --> 00:38:38,000
I would look.

607
00:38:38,040 --> 00:38:39,720
Oh. Oh!

608
00:38:39,760 --> 00:38:42,920
Listen, boss,
if you ever get into a jam...

609
00:38:42,960 --> 00:38:45,680
you need some backup again,
then you give me a call.

610
00:38:45,720 --> 00:38:48,720
Any time, day or night,
I'm your man.

611
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:07,920
VERNA: Nice place you got here.

612
00:39:09,200 --> 00:39:11,040
HARRY: I'm glad you like it.

613
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:15,320
I have to hand it to you.
You always land on your feet.

614
00:39:16,440 --> 00:39:20,000
Verna, I live over the garage.

615
00:39:20,960 --> 00:39:24,120
Jack Ames owns the place.
I just work here, more or less.

616
00:39:24,160 --> 00:39:25,240
You need stitches.

617
00:39:25,280 --> 00:39:28,600
I brought his daughter back from
Mexico a couple of years ago...

618
00:39:28,640 --> 00:39:33,000
and I was in pretty bad shape,
so he let me hole up here.

619
00:39:34,440 --> 00:39:36,800
Then he got sick,
and I was helping out.

620
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:39,200
VERNA:
That's the best I can do.

621
00:39:42,720 --> 00:39:44,640
Actually,
there's more to it than that.

622
00:39:44,640 --> 00:39:46,840
It's time I was leaving.

623
00:39:46,880 --> 00:39:48,800
VERNA: That's that actress.

624
00:39:48,800 --> 00:39:50,920
Catherine Hayward, right?

625
00:39:50,960 --> 00:39:52,120
Yeah.

626
00:39:52,160 --> 00:39:54,760
VERNA: Didn't she used to be
married to that actor...

627
00:39:54,800 --> 00:39:56,600
He disappeared.
What was his name?

628
00:39:56,640 --> 00:39:58,880
-Billy Sullivan.
-Yeah.

629
00:39:58,920 --> 00:40:00,800
HARRY: That was 20 years ago.

630
00:40:00,840 --> 00:40:03,200
Bet she doesn't look
like this anymore.

631
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:04,680
HARRY: Hey, she's--

632
00:40:05,640 --> 00:40:07,680
She's OK.

633
00:40:08,880 --> 00:40:13,120
OK, Harry, what are your plans?

634
00:40:13,120 --> 00:40:14,640
Got no plans.

635
00:40:14,680 --> 00:40:17,040
Come on.
What are you gonna do?

636
00:40:17,080 --> 00:40:20,640
You gonna go back to work,
renew your license? What?

637
00:40:20,680 --> 00:40:22,480
Verna...

638
00:40:22,520 --> 00:40:24,720
I was a cop for 20 years...

639
00:40:24,760 --> 00:40:26,640
a private investigator for five.

640
00:40:26,680 --> 00:40:28,440
I started out...

641
00:40:30,200 --> 00:40:33,240
with a wife and daughter,
and I ended up a drunk.

642
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:37,360
Slept in the office
and showered at the YMCA.

643
00:40:37,400 --> 00:40:39,520
You think I wanna go back
to that?

644
00:40:41,520 --> 00:40:44,320
Besides, I'm getting rusty.
I'm a danger to myself.

645
00:40:44,960 --> 00:40:46,040
I know.

646
00:40:47,280 --> 00:40:49,440
HARRY:
What's that supposed to mean?

647
00:40:56,000 --> 00:40:57,880
You used to be a better liar.

648
00:40:57,920 --> 00:40:59,440
Really?

649
00:41:00,400 --> 00:41:03,440
Lester lvar didn't have asthma.

650
00:41:03,480 --> 00:41:04,600
He had emphysema...

651
00:41:04,640 --> 00:41:07,000
which you'd have known
if you worked for him.

652
00:41:07,520 --> 00:41:09,680
We're gonna have
to question Jack Ames.

653
00:41:09,720 --> 00:41:10,960
His wife, too, probably.

654
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:12,280
He's really sick.

655
00:41:12,320 --> 00:41:14,160
Come on. This is a murder case.

656
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:16,080
Lester lvar
was the investigating officer...

657
00:41:16,120 --> 00:41:17,800
when Billy Sullivan disappeared.

658
00:41:17,840 --> 00:41:21,160
Lester lvar was on the force
for 30 years.

659
00:41:21,200 --> 00:41:23,200
He had a thousand cases
like this.

660
00:41:23,240 --> 00:41:24,800
What makes this one special?

661
00:41:24,840 --> 00:41:26,160
VERNA: You, Harry.

662
00:41:26,200 --> 00:41:29,240
You're the guy who showed up
at lvar's house.

663
00:41:29,280 --> 00:41:31,040
You're the guy who led me here.

664
00:41:31,080 --> 00:41:34,600
Like you say,
you're getting rusty.

665
00:41:37,400 --> 00:41:40,280
HARRY: The only person I could
think of who could help me...

666
00:41:40,320 --> 00:41:41,920
was Raymond Hope.

667
00:41:41,960 --> 00:41:43,360
Plus, he owed me.

668
00:41:43,400 --> 00:41:45,880
Or I owed him.
I couldn't figure out which.

669
00:41:45,920 --> 00:41:49,200
It was Raymond who pulled me off
the barstool...

670
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:52,640
I was living on two years ago
and introduced me to the Ameses.

671
00:41:52,680 --> 00:41:54,400
Seen in a certain light...

672
00:41:54,440 --> 00:41:57,760
everything that had happened
since then was his fault.

673
00:41:57,800 --> 00:41:59,200
Maybe I'd tell him that.

674
00:42:04,840 --> 00:42:07,840
You always were a showoff,
Raymond.

675
00:42:07,880 --> 00:42:09,080
RAYMOND: Harry?

676
00:42:09,120 --> 00:42:13,120
I almost peed on one of the few
remaining friends I have.

677
00:42:21,280 --> 00:42:23,360
Hotshot.

678
00:42:23,400 --> 00:42:26,040
HARRY: Your sprinkler fritzed,
or are you just lazy?

679
00:42:26,080 --> 00:42:28,920
RAYMOND: Don't you know better
than to walk underneath a man--

680
00:42:28,960 --> 00:42:31,440
Jesus. Look at you.

681
00:42:31,480 --> 00:42:34,680
Well, somebody disagreed
with me from behind.

682
00:42:34,720 --> 00:42:38,480
RAYMOND: No shit. Let's go
find him and disagree back.

683
00:42:38,520 --> 00:42:41,400
HARRY: [Snickers]
You any tougher than you look?

684
00:42:41,440 --> 00:42:45,080
RAYMOND: Hell, yes.
Least I used to be.

685
00:42:45,120 --> 00:42:48,880
HARRY: I used to be.
We all used to be.

686
00:42:48,960 --> 00:42:50,360
Then have a drink.

687
00:42:50,400 --> 00:42:52,200
You still a bourbon man?

688
00:42:52,240 --> 00:42:53,680
Take a ginger ale.

689
00:42:53,760 --> 00:42:56,360
Do I look like a man
who'd have a ginger ale?

690
00:42:56,400 --> 00:42:57,720
Water.

691
00:42:57,760 --> 00:42:59,160
That I can handle.

692
00:42:59,200 --> 00:43:01,080
[Big band jazz playing]

693
00:43:01,120 --> 00:43:03,480
It gonna bother you if I drink?

694
00:43:03,520 --> 00:43:05,080
HARRY: Go ahead.

695
00:43:09,200 --> 00:43:11,120
HARRY: Nice place you got here.

696
00:43:12,080 --> 00:43:14,000
Sure beats Los Feliz.

697
00:43:15,200 --> 00:43:16,840
You're above the smog.

698
00:43:16,880 --> 00:43:19,760
RAYMOND: I like to think
I'm up above a lot of things...

699
00:43:19,800 --> 00:43:21,080
since I retired.

700
00:43:23,400 --> 00:43:24,720
RAYMOND: So...

701
00:43:24,760 --> 00:43:27,880
you were playing things pretty
close to your vest last night.

702
00:43:27,920 --> 00:43:29,320
Are you in trouble?

703
00:43:29,360 --> 00:43:31,720
HARRY:
Oh, nothing I can't handle.

704
00:43:31,760 --> 00:43:33,160
It's just that...

705
00:43:33,200 --> 00:43:34,280
RAYMOND: Jack.

706
00:43:34,320 --> 00:43:36,080
Yeah, I figured that much.

707
00:43:37,040 --> 00:43:41,560
And you wanna talk to me
about Jack and Lester lvar.

708
00:43:41,600 --> 00:43:43,400
OK.

709
00:43:43,440 --> 00:43:47,240
You probably know that lvar
was the investigating officer...

710
00:43:47,280 --> 00:43:49,200
when Billy Sullivan
killed himself.

711
00:43:49,240 --> 00:43:51,440
Can't call it suicide.
They never found a body.

712
00:43:51,480 --> 00:43:54,320
L.A. Times called it a suicide.
That's good enough for me.

713
00:43:54,360 --> 00:43:55,760
HARRY: But not good enough...

714
00:43:55,800 --> 00:43:56,880
RAYMOND: For Lester lvar.

715
00:43:56,920 --> 00:43:59,080
Yeah, Lester didn't believe
in good luck...

716
00:43:59,120 --> 00:44:00,520
never having had any himself.

717
00:44:00,560 --> 00:44:05,200
Billy's suicide was good luck
for Jack and Catherine.

718
00:44:05,240 --> 00:44:07,640
With him out of the way,
they could get married.

719
00:44:07,680 --> 00:44:12,040
Lester couldn't believe the way
it worked out so smooth.

720
00:44:12,080 --> 00:44:14,360
I have never been
a great believer in luck--

721
00:44:14,400 --> 00:44:16,280
not as a way
of explaining things.

722
00:44:16,320 --> 00:44:18,200
Anyway, he's dead now.

723
00:44:18,240 --> 00:44:20,160
End of story.

724
00:44:20,160 --> 00:44:22,000
HARRY: Would be...

725
00:44:22,040 --> 00:44:25,200
if I hadn't passed those
suspicions on to Verna.

726
00:44:25,240 --> 00:44:26,880
Forgive me, Harry...

727
00:44:26,920 --> 00:44:29,480
but it sounds
like you passed them on to you.

728
00:44:32,800 --> 00:44:34,520
RAYMOND: By the way...

729
00:44:34,560 --> 00:44:39,480
I heard a rumor I didn't want
to believe was true, so...

730
00:44:39,520 --> 00:44:41,760
I thought I'd ask you directly.

731
00:44:41,800 --> 00:44:43,680
The way it was told to me...

732
00:44:43,680 --> 00:44:47,440
when you were down in Mexico
bringing the Ames kid back?

733
00:44:47,480 --> 00:44:49,880
She, uh, she...

734
00:44:49,920 --> 00:44:51,840
She shot your pecker off.

735
00:44:54,880 --> 00:44:56,160
Harry.

736
00:44:59,520 --> 00:45:00,880
Harry!

737
00:45:02,400 --> 00:45:03,800
RAYMOND: Harry!

738
00:45:05,240 --> 00:45:08,560
No. I'm fine.

739
00:45:08,600 --> 00:45:11,920
But thanks for telling me.
That explains a lot.

740
00:45:11,960 --> 00:45:14,800
RAYMOND: I'm glad to hear it.
Keep me posted, huh?

741
00:45:14,840 --> 00:45:17,200
Like you said,
Jack and I go way back.

742
00:45:17,240 --> 00:45:20,560
If there's anything I could
do for him, I would.

743
00:45:20,600 --> 00:45:23,000
And I'm glad
nobody shot your pecker off.

744
00:45:23,040 --> 00:45:24,440
Me, too!

745
00:45:30,360 --> 00:45:32,400
Me, too.

746
00:45:32,440 --> 00:45:33,640
[Starts engine]

747
00:45:51,800 --> 00:45:53,200
How you feeling?

748
00:45:55,480 --> 00:45:57,520
My husband had a heart attack...

749
00:45:57,560 --> 00:46:00,400
and the doctors ordered him
to stay in the hospital...

750
00:46:00,440 --> 00:46:03,200
and the nurses advised him
to stay in the hospital.

751
00:46:03,240 --> 00:46:05,120
I pleaded with him to stay.

752
00:46:05,160 --> 00:46:08,720
So naturally,
he's on the way home.

753
00:46:08,760 --> 00:46:10,800
That's not what I meant.

754
00:46:12,040 --> 00:46:13,520
I know what you meant.

755
00:46:16,200 --> 00:46:17,400
Fact is, l...

756
00:46:17,440 --> 00:46:18,600
Catherine?

757
00:46:19,560 --> 00:46:21,240
The ambulance is here.

758
00:46:23,080 --> 00:46:24,280
Excuse me.

759
00:46:31,720 --> 00:46:34,640
You wouldn't be falling in love
with my mother, would you?

760
00:46:39,880 --> 00:46:41,160
MEL: Poor you.

761
00:46:49,720 --> 00:46:50,840
I'm curious.

762
00:46:50,880 --> 00:46:53,760
What kind of man fucks
his dying best friend's wife?

763
00:46:55,080 --> 00:46:57,120
Not a good one.

764
00:46:58,280 --> 00:47:00,440
How long has this been going on?

765
00:47:01,920 --> 00:47:05,080
JACK: Bet you've been sleeping
together since I've been sick.

766
00:47:06,080 --> 00:47:07,240
One night.

767
00:47:07,280 --> 00:47:08,440
[Sighs]

768
00:47:10,720 --> 00:47:13,240
If you had an ounce
of decency in you...

769
00:47:13,280 --> 00:47:15,360
you'd have left this house
by now.

770
00:47:17,000 --> 00:47:19,480
Catherine know
you're being blackmailed?

771
00:47:20,960 --> 00:47:23,520
There's precious little
that Catherine doesn't know.

772
00:47:24,160 --> 00:47:26,400
What she doesn't know,
she suspects.

773
00:47:28,160 --> 00:47:30,240
JACK:
I'm the one that never suspects.

774
00:47:33,600 --> 00:47:36,800
HARRY: I delivered the envelope
to Gloria last night.

775
00:47:38,880 --> 00:47:40,600
She's lovely.

