to believe this?

1012
01:02:50,040 --> 01:02:51,920
[Verna clears throat]

1013
01:02:57,360 --> 01:02:59,160
OK.

1014
01:02:59,200 --> 01:03:02,480
So just between us--
the truth?

1015
01:03:03,440 --> 01:03:05,560
For old time's sake?

1016
01:03:05,600 --> 01:03:09,520
Did it ever strike you this
is a lousy way to make a living?

1017
01:03:11,840 --> 01:03:14,280
You start out thinking
you're going to win a few...

1018
01:03:14,320 --> 01:03:15,760
but mostly, it's...

1019
01:03:16,840 --> 01:03:18,960
It's just like tonight--

1020
01:03:19,000 --> 01:03:21,840
watching people
run out of the...

1021
01:03:22,920 --> 01:03:25,720
Iittle bit of luck
that they got left.

1022
01:03:25,760 --> 01:03:28,400
You think you're going to beat
the odds, but you don't...

1023
01:03:28,440 --> 01:03:30,720
or not very often.

1024
01:03:30,760 --> 01:03:33,280
OFFlCER: Excuse me, Lieutenant.
The captain's on his way.

1025
01:03:35,840 --> 01:03:37,760
God help you, Harry.

1026
01:03:41,840 --> 01:03:43,280
Let me go, Verna.

1027
01:03:43,360 --> 01:03:45,160
Not a chance.

1028
01:03:45,200 --> 01:03:48,800
