1034
01:04:01,280 --> 01:04:03,640
You got to give me some time...

1035
01:04:03,640 --> 01:04:07,040
so I can find
whoever did it and...

1036
01:04:07,080 --> 01:04:09,760
I don't know, square things up
at least a little bit.

1037
01:04:16,960 --> 01:04:19,480
Hey, what's-your-name,
get him out of here.

1038
01:04:19,520 --> 01:04:20,680
OFFlCER: The captain said--

1039
01:04:20,720 --> 01:04:22,760
I said get him out of here.

1040
01:04:28,000 --> 01:04:29,240
VERNA: Harry.

1041
01:04:29,280 --> 01:04:31,200
[Flushes toilet]

1042
01:04:37,720 --> 01:04:40,280
HARRY: Reuben,
I need you to meet me.

1043
01:04:41,880 --> 01:04:43,920
Three-six-double-0-one
Mulholland Highway.

1044
01:04:43,960 --> 01:04:46,320
It's above the canyon.
How soon can you get there?

1045
01:04:48,320 --> 01:04:49,760
OK, and...

1046
01:04:51,080 --> 01:04:53,240
Bring my gun. I might need it.

1047
01:04:57,520 --> 01:05:00,400
REUBEN: You mind telling me
what we're looking for?

1048
01:05:01,880 --> 01:05:03,280
REUBEN: I guess not.

1049
01:05:05,400 --> 01:05:09,160
REUBEN: Hey, listen, boss,
I got to tell you something, OK?

1050
01:05:09,200 --> 01:05:10,640
Sure.

1051
01:05:10,720 --> 01:05:14,160
REUBEN: I hope you're not going
to be mad at me, but...

1052
01:05:14,200 --> 01:05:15,680
the thing is...

1053
01:05:18,440 --> 01:05:20,600
after we crack this case...

1054
01:05:20,600 --> 01:05:23,480
I'm going to find
another line of work...

1055
01:05:23,480 --> 01:05:24,800
if that's OK with you.

1056
01:05:25,840 --> 01:05:27,560
It's OK with me.

1057
01:05:27,600 --> 01:05:29,040
REUBEN: I don't know, man...

1058
01:05:29,960 --> 01:05:31,880
Watching that lady die tonight--

1059
01:05:33,600 --> 01:05:35,520
I can't get it out of my head.

1060
01:05:36,880 --> 01:05:38,000
Yeah.

1061
01:05:39,360 --> 01:05:42,080
I know you had been
counting on me, but--

1062
01:05:42,120 --> 01:05:43,600
I said it was OK.

1063
01:05:43,640 --> 01:05:46,920
REUBEN: You don't think
that I'm, like...a coward?

1064
01:05:48,200 --> 01:05:49,640
Not for a second.

1065
01:05:50,120 --> 01:05:52,760
I guess we can still be friends,
right?

1066
01:05:52,800 --> 01:05:53,920
We can still--

1067
01:05:53,960 --> 01:05:55,360
[Shovel strikes object]

1068
01:05:56,840 --> 01:05:57,920
Harry?

1069
01:06:17,920 --> 01:06:19,200
REUBEN: Ohh.

1070
01:06:27,560 --> 01:06:29,120
What do we do now, Harry?

1071
01:06:32,000 --> 01:06:33,400
Cover it up.

1072
01:06:33,920 --> 01:06:36,600
I know I'm the one that keeps
flunking the P.I. exam...

1073
01:06:36,640 --> 01:06:38,400
but when something
like this happens...

1074
01:06:38,440 --> 01:06:39,720
shouldn't you call the cops?

1075
01:06:39,760 --> 01:06:41,400
HARRY: I said cover it up.

1076
01:06:41,400 --> 01:06:44,480
REUBEN: That's a bullet hole.
Don't you wanna know who it is?

1077
01:06:44,520 --> 01:06:46,240
HARRY: I know who it is.

1078
01:07:08,880 --> 01:07:11,720
The thing you just don't get
about Jack and Catherine...

1079
01:07:11,760 --> 01:07:14,520
is they live for each other.

1080
01:07:14,560 --> 01:07:16,920
They have the starring roles
in their own lives...

1081
01:07:18,040 --> 01:07:19,960
and you're just a bit player.

1082
01:07:21,400 --> 01:07:22,840
Me, too.

1083
01:07:24,160 --> 01:07:26,480
MEL: It's their love story,
not yours.

1084
01:07:28,120 --> 01:07:30,640
You don't get to kiss the girl
in the end.

1085
01:07:31,840 --> 01:07:33,720
She's somebody else's girl.

1086
01:07:40,600 --> 01:07:43,800
JACK: You'll be pleased to know
I've decided to do chemotherapy.

1087
01:07:44,560 --> 01:07:47,280
It worked before, so...

1088
01:07:47,320 --> 01:07:48,960
you never know.

1089
01:07:53,320 --> 01:07:55,480
At least
I thought you'd be pleased.

1090
01:07:55,480 --> 01:07:58,800
We found Billy Sullivan
last night...

1091
01:07:58,840 --> 01:08:00,440
or what's left of him.

1092
01:08:06,000 --> 01:08:08,760
I guess I've been expecting that
for 20 years.

1093
01:08:10,520 --> 01:08:12,800
JACK: Look, you can think
what you like.

1094
01:08:15,720 --> 01:08:19,720
It wasn't murder. It wasn't
like you murder somebody.

1095
01:08:22,240 --> 01:08:24,600
Catherine and l
had fallen in love.

1096
01:08:27,080 --> 01:08:29,680
As you know, Catherine's
easy to fall in love with.

1097
01:08:33,120 --> 01:08:35,480
Eventually, Billy found out
about it and came after me.

1098
01:08:35,520 --> 01:08:37,200
I was staying out at the ranch.

1099
01:08:37,840 --> 01:08:39,880
Suddenly, I turn around,
and there he is...

1100
01:08:39,920 --> 01:08:43,280
so drunk he can hardly stand up,
swearing he's going to kill me.

1101
01:08:44,920 --> 01:08:46,640
The swimming pool was empty.

1102
01:08:48,560 --> 01:08:50,600
You should've heard the sound
his head made...

1103
01:08:50,640 --> 01:08:51,960
when he hit the bottom.

1104
01:08:53,600 --> 01:08:56,520
You should've seen the way
he lay there and didn't move.

1105
01:08:56,560 --> 01:09:00,240
One second is all it took
and his life was snuffed out.

1106
01:09:02,920 --> 01:09:04,360
You are good.

1107
01:09:06,160 --> 01:09:08,080
You are very good.

1108
01:09:09,240 --> 01:09:11,880
And I would've believed you,
except I saw the corpse.

1109
01:09:11,920 --> 01:09:13,640
What are you talking about?

1110
01:09:14,080 --> 01:09:16,440
There's a bullet hole
in the back of his head.

1111
01:09:16,480 --> 01:09:18,680
-That's impossible.
-Nope.

1112
01:09:18,720 --> 01:09:21,760
Did you bother to go down
and see whether he was alive?

1113
01:09:24,080 --> 01:09:25,520
HARRY: Of course not.

1114
01:09:25,560 --> 01:09:28,440
There was blood and a body.
You didn't want any part of it.

1115
01:09:28,440 --> 01:09:31,680
You wanted someone to come along
and make it all go away.

1116
01:09:32,480 --> 01:09:34,840
So you called Raymond Hope.
What'd he say?

1117
01:09:34,880 --> 01:09:36,880
Told me to get out of there.

1118
01:09:36,920 --> 01:09:39,200
And he'd come clean up the mess.

1119
01:09:41,600 --> 01:09:46,840
But Raymond...
Iived in Los Feliz back then.

1120
01:09:46,840 --> 01:09:50,360
It would've taken him--what--
an hour to get there?

1121
01:09:50,400 --> 01:09:51,840
Who else did you call?

1122
01:09:55,960 --> 01:09:57,640
If you harm her in any way...

1123
01:09:57,680 --> 01:10:00,040
I swear I'll come back
from the grave...

1124
01:10:00,080 --> 01:10:02,200
and I won't be in
a fucking wheelchair, either.

1125
01:10:13,560 --> 01:10:15,480
[Puts out cigarette]

1126
01:10:18,320 --> 01:10:20,520
Quick, come look at the sun.

1127
01:10:20,560 --> 01:10:23,320
See it hanging there
half an inch above the horizon?

1128
01:10:23,320 --> 01:10:25,720
Looks like it's gonna be there
forever, doesn't it?

1129
01:10:28,280 --> 01:10:29,520
You look tired.

1130
01:10:29,560 --> 01:10:31,920
HARRY: Yeah. I am tired.

1131
01:10:32,480 --> 01:10:34,360
I'm tired of people
getting killed.

1132
01:10:34,400 --> 01:10:36,280
I'm tired of being lied to.

1133
01:10:36,320 --> 01:10:38,200
When have I lied to you?

1134
01:10:38,240 --> 01:10:40,440
When you acted
as though you loved me.

1135
01:10:40,480 --> 01:10:43,800
Whereas, I love my husband?
That's what I'm accused of?

1136
01:10:43,800 --> 01:10:46,440
I never made it a secret
that I love my husband.

1137
01:10:46,480 --> 01:10:48,040
Enough to kill for?

1138
01:10:48,080 --> 01:10:49,440
You bet.

1139
01:10:51,800 --> 01:10:54,200
CATHERlNE: Feel better
now that we've cleared that up?

1140
01:10:54,680 --> 01:10:56,200
I don't feel worse.

1141
01:10:56,240 --> 01:10:57,320
Well, then...

1142
01:10:58,360 --> 01:11:01,000
why don't you just ask me
some more questions?

1143
01:11:01,040 --> 01:11:02,160
Feel free.

1144
01:11:04,800 --> 01:11:06,320
HARRY:
You'll tell me the truth?

1145
01:11:06,360 --> 01:11:07,440
CATHERlNE: Yes.

1146
01:11:13,040 --> 01:11:14,360
Did you kill Lester lvar?

1147
01:11:14,400 --> 01:11:17,000
No. Next question.

1148
01:11:17,040 --> 01:11:18,760
Did you have him killed?

1149
01:11:18,800 --> 01:11:21,280
No. Next question.

1150
01:11:21,320 --> 01:11:23,120
Did you kill Jeff Willis
or have him killed?

1151
01:11:23,160 --> 01:11:24,560
No. Next.

1152
01:11:25,640 --> 01:11:27,080
Twenty years ago...

1153
01:11:28,200 --> 01:11:31,040
and Jack called to tell you what
happened to Billy Sullivan--

1154
01:11:31,080 --> 01:11:33,600
Did I drive to the ranch,
find Billy still alive...

1155
01:11:33,640 --> 01:11:36,440
put a gun to his head,
and pull the trigger?

1156
01:11:36,440 --> 01:11:37,560
No.

1157
01:11:38,120 --> 01:11:41,760
I said I loved my husband enough
that I would kill for him...

1158
01:11:41,800 --> 01:11:43,080
not that I did.

1159
01:11:45,840 --> 01:11:48,720
Now let me ask you something.

1160
01:11:50,680 --> 01:11:52,240
Do you believe me?

1161
01:11:52,280 --> 01:11:53,640
[Chuckles]

1162
01:11:54,520 --> 01:11:55,960
I'll tell you what I believe.

1163
01:11:58,720 --> 01:12:00,280
I believe that you're smart...

1164
01:12:02,360 --> 01:12:03,960
and you're beautiful and rich.

1165
01:12:04,000 --> 01:12:06,640
I believe that life
has worked out for you...

1166
01:12:06,680 --> 01:12:08,840
in ways that it doesn't
for most people.

1167
01:12:08,880 --> 01:12:12,640
I think people like you get used
to having it work out for you.

1168
01:12:13,840 --> 01:12:16,240
After a while, you begin to...

1169
01:12:16,280 --> 01:12:18,720
think you're entitled to all
the things you got.

1170
01:12:18,760 --> 01:12:21,880
CATHERlNE: You think I care
about anything in this house...

1171
01:12:21,880 --> 01:12:23,520
but my husband?

1172
01:12:24,640 --> 01:12:25,760
CATHERlNE: You think...

1173
01:12:26,840 --> 01:12:32,560
You think people like me
care so much about things...

1174
01:12:33,640 --> 01:12:35,080
that we would kill for them?

1175
01:12:36,760 --> 01:12:38,360
Is that what you think?

1176
01:12:39,160 --> 01:12:42,040
That I just care about things,
Harry?

1177
01:12:44,680 --> 01:12:47,240
Is that what you think?

1178
01:12:47,280 --> 01:12:49,840
That I care about
all these things?

1179
01:12:49,880 --> 01:12:52,480
All these fucking goddamned...

1180
01:12:55,000 --> 01:12:56,160
things?

1181
01:13:01,440 --> 01:13:02,920
Then maybe people like you...

1182
01:13:02,960 --> 01:13:05,320
shouldn't get close
to people like me.

1183
01:13:25,640 --> 01:13:26,920
You wanna come inside...

1184
01:13:26,960 --> 01:13:28,880
or do you like it better
out there?

1185
01:13:31,800 --> 01:13:34,040
When was the last time
that we went fishing?

1186
01:13:34,080 --> 01:13:36,560
You tell me.

1187
01:13:36,600 --> 01:13:38,040
HARRY: It's too long.

1188
01:13:39,840 --> 01:13:41,640
Let's go.

1189
01:13:41,680 --> 01:13:44,280
Right now, you and me,
head down to Baja.

1190
01:13:44,320 --> 01:13:45,720
Fine.

1191
01:13:45,720 --> 01:13:47,080
Let's have a drink first.

1192
01:13:47,120 --> 01:13:49,040
Got ginger ale in the fridge.

1193
01:13:55,000 --> 01:13:56,520
I'll take bourbon.

1194
01:13:57,120 --> 01:13:58,600
Things that bad?

1195
01:13:59,160 --> 01:14:02,200
You said I might learn something
I didn't want to know.

1196
01:14:03,960 --> 01:14:05,200
Catherine.

1197
01:14:07,320 --> 01:14:09,000
RAYMOND:
You going to turn her in?

1198
01:14:09,040 --> 01:14:10,840
HARRY: I thought about it...

1199
01:14:10,880 --> 01:14:13,400
then I decided
to go fishing instead.

1200
01:14:13,440 --> 01:14:16,480
RAYMOND: That would be
the sensible thing.

1201
01:14:18,720 --> 01:14:19,880
I mean, screw it.

1202
01:14:20,640 --> 01:14:22,840
Everybody pretty much got
what they deserved.

1203
01:14:22,840 --> 01:14:25,720
If we leave soon, we could
be deep in Baja by morning.

1204
01:14:26,080 --> 01:14:29,080
We ought to take the Explorer.
Your beater will never make it.

1205
01:14:29,120 --> 01:14:31,160
Lester lvar was a crooked cop.

1206
01:14:31,200 --> 01:14:33,840
It's my hunch he was
trying to shake Jack down.

1207
01:14:33,880 --> 01:14:35,200
RAYMOND: The marlin
are running about now.

1208
01:14:35,240 --> 01:14:36,800
I know a guy
who'll take us out...

1209
01:14:36,840 --> 01:14:39,360
for 80 bucks a day
and a case of American beer.

1210
01:14:39,840 --> 01:14:43,200
But the funny thing...

1211
01:14:43,240 --> 01:14:45,240
is that...

1212
01:14:45,280 --> 01:14:48,240
you know,
Lester lived in a rat hole.

1213
01:14:48,280 --> 01:14:50,520
You'd think
if he was on the take, he'd...

1214
01:14:52,120 --> 01:14:55,800
You'd think he'd have a place
that would be more like...

1215
01:14:59,800 --> 01:15:02,280
more like this.

1216
01:15:11,320 --> 01:15:13,040
You haven't touched your drink.

1217
01:15:13,080 --> 01:15:16,080
HARRY:
Raymond, this is not easy...

1218
01:15:16,120 --> 01:15:19,520
but you did a lot more
than clean up Jack's mess...

1219
01:15:19,560 --> 01:15:20,880
didn't you?

1220
01:15:20,920 --> 01:15:23,520
Not a lot more.

1221
01:15:23,560 --> 01:15:24,840
Sullivan was going to wind up...

1222
01:15:24,880 --> 01:15:26,920
in a wheelchair
the rest of his life.

1223
01:15:26,960 --> 01:15:29,800
I ended his misery, Harry.
I did him a favor.

1224
01:15:29,840 --> 01:15:31,280
You see, I think...

1225
01:15:31,320 --> 01:15:34,960
that on that long drive
out to the ranch...

1226
01:15:35,000 --> 01:15:36,720
you began spending that money...

1227
01:15:36,760 --> 01:15:39,480
Jack was gonna pay you
to keep him out of jail.

1228
01:15:39,960 --> 01:15:41,240
I think that...

1229
01:15:42,920 --> 01:15:45,920
you bought this place
in your head...

1230
01:15:45,960 --> 01:15:47,440
on that ride.

1231
01:15:48,440 --> 01:15:50,880
And then, when you got there...

1232
01:15:50,920 --> 01:15:53,640
you found out
Billy Sullivan wasn't dead.

1233
01:15:55,120 --> 01:15:57,960
You knew you'd lose it
before you could move in.

1234
01:15:59,040 --> 01:16:01,440
They really got to you,
didn't they?

1235
01:16:01,480 --> 01:16:03,040
I can understand
about Catherine.

1236
01:16:03,080 --> 01:16:05,760
A woman like that can twist
a man's pecker into a knot...

1237
01:16:05,800 --> 01:16:06,880
I'll grant you.

1238
01:16:06,920 --> 01:16:10,240
And Jack's a charming guy,
but I got to ask you, Harry--

1239
01:16:10,280 --> 01:16:12,680
don't you ever get tired
of the beautiful people?

1240
01:16:12,720 --> 01:16:13,800
Doesn't it ever bother you...

1241
01:16:13,840 --> 01:16:16,800
that the Jacks and Catherines
of this world do as they want...

1242
01:16:16,840 --> 01:16:19,400
because guys like you and me
clean up after them?

1243
01:16:21,680 --> 01:16:24,440
Jack Ames couldn't
get blood out of a sock...

1244
01:16:24,480 --> 01:16:27,920
with a washing machine
and a gallon of Clorox.

1245
01:16:27,960 --> 01:16:31,120
Me?
I can get blood out of a sock.

1246
01:16:31,160 --> 01:16:33,040
That's what I do.

1247
01:16:33,080 --> 01:16:36,080
I clean up messes,
and I get paid for it.

1248
01:16:36,120 --> 01:16:39,320
You imagine it different,
but you're the same as me.

1249
01:16:40,920 --> 01:16:43,320
RAYMOND: You think it was
Catherine who seduced you.

1250
01:16:43,360 --> 01:16:45,440
It was both of them, Harry.

1251
01:16:45,480 --> 01:16:47,400
It was the whole package.

1252
01:16:49,520 --> 01:16:51,120
Ah...

1253
01:16:52,280 --> 01:16:54,040
I know.

1254
01:16:54,080 --> 01:16:55,600
I was the same way.

1255
01:16:56,680 --> 01:16:58,080
Let's face it--

1256
01:16:58,120 --> 01:17:01,400
there's them, and there's us...

1257
01:17:01,440 --> 01:17:04,880
and right now, the thing for us
to do is go fishing.

1258
01:17:05,520 --> 01:17:08,240
I'd like to, Raymond, but--

1259
01:17:08,280 --> 01:17:10,560
You know how many times
I didn't kill you...

1260
01:17:10,600 --> 01:17:12,040
the past couple of days?

1261
01:17:15,120 --> 01:17:16,240
OK.

1262
01:17:17,440 --> 01:17:20,480
I'll wait until I get into town
before I call Verna.

1263
01:17:20,520 --> 01:17:22,200
You can make a run for it.

1264
01:17:22,240 --> 01:17:26,440
Oh, I can't do that, Harry,
not at my age.

1265
01:17:27,080 --> 01:17:29,800
Besides, for what it's worth,
you were right.

1266
01:17:30,600 --> 01:17:33,200
I couldn't give up this place.

1267
01:17:33,240 --> 01:17:36,040
Not then...not now.

1268
01:17:39,960 --> 01:17:42,320
Well...shit.

1269
01:17:42,360 --> 01:17:45,360
I know.
It's a bitch, isn't it?

1270
01:17:47,200 --> 01:17:48,640
Good luck, hotshot.

1271
01:17:49,600 --> 01:17:50,840
Good luck to you.

1272
01:17:52,840 --> 01:17:55,440
I can see your reflection
in the glass.

1273
01:17:56,720 --> 01:17:58,720
Funny, the things
you don't think about...

1274
01:17:58,760 --> 01:18:00,360
when you're buying a house.

1275
01:18:48,360 --> 01:18:49,720
[Knock knock]

1276
01:18:51,480 --> 01:18:53,000
JACK: Oh, thank God.

1277
01:18:53,040 --> 01:18:55,920
I hate playing solitaire.
I can't stop cheating.

1278
01:18:57,320 --> 01:19:00,680
One hand for everything
that we own.

1279
01:19:03,480 --> 01:19:06,000
Do I have anything you want?

1280
01:19:06,040 --> 01:19:07,240
Yeah, your health.

1281
01:19:08,280 --> 01:19:09,480
[Shuffles cards]

1282
01:19:09,520 --> 01:19:12,160
Deal them, for Christ's sake,
before you wear the spots off.

1283
01:19:18,160 --> 01:19:20,680
I had to shoot
Raymond Hope tonight.

1284
01:19:23,440 --> 01:19:24,760
Dead?

1285
01:19:24,800 --> 01:19:26,000
HARRY: Dead.

1286
01:19:27,760 --> 01:19:30,040
Turns out
he killed Billy Sullivan...

1287
01:19:32,080 --> 01:19:34,080
so you can rest easy
about Catherine.

1288
01:19:35,600 --> 01:19:38,080
I've always rested easy
about Catherine.

1289
01:19:39,680 --> 01:19:41,600
If she had murdered him...

1290
01:19:42,760 --> 01:19:44,480
it wouldn't matter to you,
would it?

1291
01:19:44,520 --> 01:19:45,760
JACK: No.

1292
01:19:46,920 --> 01:19:48,920
Is that the difference
between us, you think?

1293
01:19:48,960 --> 01:19:52,440
Right, wrong, truth--
doesn't mean anything to you?

1294
01:19:52,480 --> 01:19:54,840
Tonight, my daughter told me
that she loves me.

1295
01:19:54,880 --> 01:19:56,480
You think that's true?

1296
01:19:57,040 --> 01:19:58,240
I'm sure of it.

1297
01:19:58,280 --> 01:20:00,760
My wife says she loves me.

1298
01:20:00,800 --> 01:20:02,280
Is that true?

1299
01:20:03,320 --> 01:20:04,640
Yes.

1300
01:20:04,680 --> 01:20:06,560
Are you sure?

1301
01:20:08,320 --> 01:20:09,880
I'm sure.

1302
01:20:09,920 --> 01:20:11,360
Me, too.

1303
01:20:12,360 --> 01:20:13,800
And you?

1304
01:20:15,800 --> 01:20:17,440
You say you're my friend.

1305
01:20:20,280 --> 01:20:21,760
Is that the truth?

1306
01:20:24,000 --> 01:20:25,800
That's the truth.

1307
01:20:25,840 --> 01:20:27,680
I'm satisfied.

1308
01:20:31,240 --> 01:20:33,000
Enough truth.

1309
01:20:36,880 --> 01:20:39,280
You prick, you.

1310
01:20:39,320 --> 01:20:41,000
You've got gin, haven't you?

1311
01:20:44,080 --> 01:20:45,360
Fuck you.

1312
01:20:45,400 --> 01:20:47,880
Just me?
Not the horse I rode in on?

1313
01:20:47,920 --> 01:20:49,240
Him, too.

1314
01:20:50,720 --> 01:20:52,400
Here, let me give you a hand.

1315
01:20:52,440 --> 01:20:53,840
I got it. I got it.

1316
01:20:57,840 --> 01:20:58,960
Ohh...

1317
01:21:03,160 --> 01:21:04,560
JACK: You know, Harry...

1318
01:21:04,600 --> 01:21:07,120
you don't have to leave.

1319
01:21:07,160 --> 01:21:08,720
Yeah, I do.

1320
01:21:11,560 --> 01:21:13,400
[Sighs] I do.

1321
01:21:15,480 --> 01:21:17,840
Do you mind hitting ""Play""
on the way out?

1322
01:21:23,640 --> 01:21:26,320
JACK:
Who's that handsome devil?

1323
01:21:26,360 --> 01:21:28,400
[Jack chuckles]

1324
01:21:29,760 --> 01:21:31,720
JACK ON TV: I'll see you.

1325
01:21:36,600 --> 01:21:39,240
JACK: Drop by
anytime you feel like it.

1326
01:21:39,280 --> 01:21:41,440
I mean it.

1327
01:21:41,480 --> 01:21:43,240
I'm feeling a lot better.

1328
01:21:46,200 --> 01:21:48,120
I may just beat this thing yet.

1329
01:21:48,160 --> 01:21:50,600
JACK ON TV:
Nobody races unless I say so.

1330
01:21:51,760 --> 01:21:53,680
That's why I'm here.

1331
01:21:53,720 --> 01:21:55,880
That's why they made me
the coach.

1332
01:21:58,800 --> 01:22:00,720
Yeah, you ski fast.

1333
01:22:00,760 --> 01:22:02,520
You race.

1334
01:22:03,560 --> 01:22:05,000
But you're reckless.

1335
01:22:06,040 --> 01:22:07,640
You crack up.

1336
01:22:07,680 --> 01:22:09,160
EGAN: That's it?

1337
01:22:10,760 --> 01:22:13,760
That's it.

1338
01:22:13,880 --> 01:22:14,960
EGAN: OK.

1339
01:22:15,040 --> 01:22:16,720
All right.
That'll conclude the interview.

1340
01:22:16,760 --> 01:22:21,280
It's October 20, 1997,
at 0600 hours.

1341
01:22:33,880 --> 01:22:36,120
But that's not quite it, is it?

1342
01:22:40,120 --> 01:22:41,560
No, not quite.

1343
01:22:44,440 --> 01:22:46,680
[Playing
The Very Thought of You]

1344
01:22:51,080 --> 01:22:52,920
After my daughter died...

1345
01:22:52,920 --> 01:22:55,800
I started hitting
the sauce pretty bad...

1346
01:22:56,440 --> 01:22:59,640
and it became obvious my wife
and I weren't going to make it.

1347
01:23:02,680 --> 01:23:06,040
It was Raymond who took me in,
let me sleep on his couch.

1348
01:23:08,040 --> 01:23:09,720
You could always
count on Raymond.

1349
01:23:13,400 --> 01:23:15,640
While I was talking to Jack,
you were talking to him.

1350
01:23:15,680 --> 01:23:18,200
You told him about Lester lvar.

1351
01:23:18,240 --> 01:23:20,160
[Stops playing]

1352
01:23:21,240 --> 01:23:22,320
[Resumes playing]

1353
01:23:22,360 --> 01:23:24,600
HARRY: You had him take care
of Willis and Gloria.

1354
01:23:24,640 --> 01:23:26,760
I never asked him
to kill anybody.

1355
01:23:26,800 --> 01:23:28,640
Yeah, but you knew he would.

1356
01:23:32,280 --> 01:23:34,520
[Plays]

1357
01:23:37,600 --> 01:23:39,440
Tell me, does it bother you...

1358
01:23:40,480 --> 01:23:42,480
that all those people
would've been alive...

1359
01:23:42,520 --> 01:23:44,120
if it weren't for you?

1360
01:23:44,160 --> 01:23:46,080
[Stops playing]

1361
01:23:50,440 --> 01:23:53,520
My husband is still alive.
That pleases me.

1362
01:23:55,760 --> 01:23:58,320
I don't think I'm to blame
for anything you've done.

1363
01:24:03,280 --> 01:24:04,600
CATHERlNE: Harry.

1364
01:24:09,280 --> 01:24:10,600
Still love me?

1365
01:24:25,600 --> 01:24:26,720
Love you, too.

1366
01:24:28,520 --> 01:24:30,000
VERNA: So...

1367
01:24:30,040 --> 01:24:33,040
Catherine Ames gets away
with it?

1368
01:24:33,080 --> 01:24:34,880
Not really.

1369
01:24:36,040 --> 01:24:37,120
VERNA: Oh.

1370
01:24:37,160 --> 01:24:39,600
Somebody ought to get away
with something.

1371
01:24:41,560 --> 01:24:43,360
Wanna buy me a cup of coffee?

1372
01:24:46,080 --> 01:24:47,520
Oh, yeah.

1373
01:24:49,920 --> 01:24:52,360
HARRY: How about the captain?
Any fallout?

1374
01:24:52,400 --> 01:24:54,160
[Verna chuckles]

1375
01:24:54,200 --> 01:24:57,600
VERNA: Let's just say I'm not
expecting a promotion soon.

1376
01:24:58,240 --> 01:25:00,360
Fuck it. It's only a career.

1377
01:25:00,400 --> 01:25:02,960
-But no discipline?
-No.

1378
01:25:03,000 --> 01:25:04,560
I got vacation time coming...

1379
01:25:04,600 --> 01:25:07,480
and it was strongly suggested
I take it.

1380
01:25:07,520 --> 01:25:09,440
HARRY: Hey.

1381
01:25:09,480 --> 01:25:11,800
I've been thinking
about going away myself.

1382
01:25:12,640 --> 01:25:13,880
I remember Catalina.

1383
01:25:13,920 --> 01:25:16,520
That was...nice.

1384
01:25:16,560 --> 01:25:18,240
How about a return engagement?

1385
01:25:19,840 --> 01:25:20,880
Maybe.

1386
01:25:25,880 --> 01:25:28,000
[Coins jingle]

1387
01:25:29,880 --> 01:25:31,280
HARRY: Oh.

1388
01:25:31,320 --> 01:25:33,520
Verna, I never knew you cared.

1389
01:25:33,560 --> 01:25:34,920
Just checking.

1390
01:25:35,040 --> 01:25:38,040
That's fair.


